            <h2><u>North Maha</u>rashtra</h2>
        </section>
        <p>North Maharashtra is a region rich in cultural diversity, known for its historical significance, vibrant
            traditions, and agricultural abundance. This area includes cities like Jalna, Nashik, and Dhule, each
            contributing to a rich cultural fabric. Renowned for its cotton and sugarcane production, North Maharashtra
            also boasts numerous historical sites, temples, and forts, which reflect its glorious past. Festivals like
            Makar Sankranti and Dussehra are celebrated with immense zeal, showcasing the community's unity and cultural
            heritage.</p>

